                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/328</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Senator <persName type="from">Couzens</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Enclosed is a page taken from
                    “The Nation”, October 24, 1923, entitled, “Mr. Hughes Makes a Secret
                        Alliance”.<note n="5" xml:id="d681fn5">Not reprinted.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I do not know whether this was sent to all the Senators or not, but in any event
                    it seems to me that what is contained in this article could hardly be correct,
                    at least not the whole story. If consistent with your office, could you give me
                    the correct information? If not consistent, will you please say if there is any
                    way by which Congress may be informed later on?</p>
                <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Couzens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
